FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778054737
OL,3,CWhat is a 'flabby high' and what is
OL,4,Cthe truth behind the 'Arctic plunge'?
OL,6,FWith an average temperature of 12C in
OL,7,Fthe north and 15C in the south in
OL,8,Fearly May, yes, we're around or a bit
OL,9,Fbelow average and yes, it will feel
OL,10,Fcolder still in the cold wind, but the
OL,11,Fdramatic drop comes more from the
OL,12,Fcomparison to the last couple of
OL,13,Fweeks, than from the fact that the
OL,14,Ftemperatures have returned to near
OL,15,Fnormal.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
