CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778054737
OL,3,CWhat is a 'flabby high' and what is
OL,4,Cthe truth behind the 'Arctic plunge'?
OL,6,FThat said, under the clearest skies,
OL,7,Ftemperatures in the early hours of
OL,8,FWednesday morning are likely to drop
OL,9,Fto around -4C across eastern Scotland
OL,10,Fand -1C in northern England, with a
OL,11,Fwidespread frost - that's not unheard
OL,12,Fof, but it's certainly less usual at
OL,13,Fthis point in the season.
OL,15,FWhy is there talk of an 'Arctic
OL,16,Fplunge'?
OL,18,FI'm going to let you into a secret
OL,19,Fthat the tabloids don't want you to
OL,20,Fknow: an 'Arctic Plunge' just means
OL,21,Fcold air moving in from the north!
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
