OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1778054737
OL,3,CWhat is a 'flabby high' and what is
OL,4,Cthe truth behind the 'Arctic plunge'?
OL,6,FAs always, our weather, and certainly
OL,7,Fthe feel of the weather, is in large
OL,8,Fpart the result of the direction of
OL,9,Fthe wind.
OL,11,FIn its most simple terms, you can tell
OL,12,Fa lot whether it will feel warm or
OL,13,Fcold by looking at the wind direction.
OL,15,FSo with winds swinging round to a cold
OL,16,Fnortherly direction throughout Tuesday
OL,17,Fand into Wednesday, the UK starts to
OL,18,Ftap into the cooler air that sits
OL,19,Facross the Arctic and it blows
OL,20,Fsouthwards on northerly winds.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
